  "prompt": "What will be my rank if I have scored 132/200 in MU-OET?",
  "response": "The rank you will receive in the MU-OET (Manipal University Online Entrance Test) depends on various factors, including the total number of test-takers and the distribution of scores. Since the specific data for each exam session varies, it's not possible to provide an exact rank without this information.\n\nHowever, you can get a rough idea by understanding that higher scores typically result in better ranks. A score of 132 out of 200 is a 66% score. If you know the percentile or the performance of others in your session, you could estimate your rank more accurately.\n\nTo get your exact rank, you should:\n1. Check the official MU-OET website for result announcements.\n2. Look for rank or percentile information provided along with your score.\n3. Contact Manipal University's admission office if you need further clarification on your rank.\n\nRemember, your rank is just one part of the admission process. Other factors like your academic record, extracurricular activities, and performance in any subsequent interviews or assessments can also influence your admission chances.",
